\index \l target="REALIA:2.8">2.8 Battle-axe\l*
\index \l target="REALIA:2.9">2.9 Helmet\l*
\index \l target="REALIA:2.10">2.10 Shields\l*
\index \l target="REALIA:2.11">2.11 Leg armor, leg protectors\l*
\index \l target="REALIA:2.12">2.12 Breastplate, chest protector\l*
\index \l target="REALIA:2.13">2.13 Scale armor, coat of mail\l*
\index \l target="REALIA:2.14">2.14 Archery\l*
\index \l target="REALIA:2.15">2.15 Chariot\l*
\index \l target="REALIA:2.16">2.16 Wooden tower on elephant\l*
\index \l target="REALIA:2.17">2.17 Standard, ensign, banner\l*
\index \l target="REALIA:2.18">2.18 Barrier, barricade, roadblock\l*
\index \l target="REALIA:2.19">2.19 Siege instruments\l*
\key 2.1
\title Weapon
\cont \u References:\u*
\heb כְּלִי
\trl kli
\ref H00104900500010 H00403501600008 H00403501800006 H00500104100046 H00700905400016 H00701801100036 H00701801600012 H00701801700090 H00900801200042 H00901400100028 H00901400700010 H00901401400024 H00901401700050 H00901705400026 H00902004000010 H00902100900040 H00903100600018 H00903100900016 H00903101000008 H01000102700012 H01001801500012 H01002303700018 H01201100800018 H01201101100014 H01202001300062 H01301000500008 H01301000900018 H01301001000008 H01301103900016 H01301203400018 H01301203800038 H01402300700022 H01900701400008 H02100901800008 H02301300500022 H02303900200064 H02305401600024 H02305401700004 H02402100400018 H02402200700014 H02405002500016 H02405102000008 H02600900100030 H02600900200032 H02603202700026
\heb נֶשֶׁק
\trl nesheq
\ref H01201000200052 H01802002400006 H02302200800028 H02603900900022 H02603901000034
\heb שֶׁלַח
\trl shelach
\ref H01402301000018 H01403200500064 H01600401100048 H01600401700038 H01803301800022 H01803601200012 H02900200800026
\cont \u Description:\u*
\line The Hebrew words in the passages listed above are generic words for “weapon.”
\line ———
\cont \u Translation:\u*
\line The Hebrew word \i kli\i* is a general term meaning “implement,” “tool,” or “vessel,” but in the passages listed above it is best rendered “weapon[s].”
\line The Hebrew word \i shelach\i* refers to weapons that are thrown or projected, such as javelins and arrows.
\key 2.2
\title Sling
\cont \u References:\u*
\heb מַרְגֵּמָה
\trl margemah
\ref H02002600800010
\heb קלע, קֶלַע, קַלָּע
\trl qala‘ (verb or noun), qela‘
\ref H00702001600032 H00901704000058 H00901704900030 H00901705000018 H00902502900054 H01200302500066 H01402601400042 H01804102000020 H03800901500020
\grk σφενδόνη, σφενδονήτης
\trl sfendonē, sfendonētēs
\ref L06800601200062 L06800900700052 L07104700400036 L07700605100050 L07700901100044
\cont \u Description:\u*
\line \fig |WEB-0379_sling.jpg|col||Gary Todd|Sling with stones|2.0\fig* The sling was a small rectangular or oval piece of leather or woven material with cords attached to the two ends. The leather or cloth was slightly smaller than a man’s hand, and the cords were about the length of an arm.
\line ———
\cont \u Usage:\u*
\line The sling was used to project a stone at high velocity at a target. The stone was placed in the pouch formed by the leather or cloth. The slinger grasped the ends of the cords and swung the stone in rapid circles. By releasing one of the cords at just the right moment, the pouch was opened and the stone was projected toward the target. Effective use of the sling required much practice. \fig |WEB-0380_slings_en.jpg|col||© Mike Peel|Soldiers with slings|2.0\fig*
\line ———
\cont \u Translation:\u*
\line If possible, translators should avoid using a word that will be under­stood as a modern slingshot or catapult made with pieces of rubber. In \s H01402601400042 H01804102801000\s*; and \s H03800901500020\s*, the focus is actually on the stones and not on the weapon. In these passages the translator may avoid mentioning the sling; for example in \s H01804102801000\s*b \a GNT\a* has “rocks thrown at him are like bits of straw.”
\line The Greek word \i sfendonētēs\i* in \s L06800601200062\s* and \s L07700901100044\s* describes not the weapon but the person who uses it, the “slinger.” In \s L06800601200062\s* \a GNT\a* says “who used a sling as a weapon.”
\line Where such a weapon is unknown, it may be possible to say “a special weapon for throwing stones.”
\key 2.3
\title Sword
\index \l target="REALIA:2.3.1">2.3.1 Sheath, scabbard\l*
\cont \u References:\u*
\heb חֶרֶב
\trl cherev
\ref H00100302400040 H00102704000006 H00103102600036 H00103402500044 H00103402600022 H00104802200032 H00200500300058 H00200502100044 H00201500900020 H00201701300022 H00201800400028 H00202002500024 H00202202300018 H00203202700022 H00302600600040 H00302600700022 H00302600800036 H00302602500008 H00302603300020 H00302603600044 H00302603700018 H00401400300030 H00401404300028 H00401901600022 H00402001800022 H00402102400012 H00402202300026 H00402202900024 H00402203100034 H00403100800066 H00501301600026 H00501301600052 H00502001300028 H00502802200042 H00503202500008 H00503204100008 H00503204200012 H00503302900026 H00600500200024 H00600500300010 H00600501300040 H00600602100056 H00600802400054 H00600802400082 H00601001100078 H00601002800030 H00601003000032 H00601003200040 H00601003500024 H00601003700014 H00601003900028 H00601101000038 H00601101100022 H00601101200038 H00601101400046 H00601302200026 H00601904700046 H00602401200038 H00700100800028 H00700102500028 H00700301600010 H00700302100022 H00700302200040 H00700401500036 H00700401600040 H00700701400020 H00700702000062 H00700702200022 H00700801000064 H00700802000028 H00700905400026 H00701802700058 H00702000200042 H00702001500038 H00702001700028 H00702002500056 H00702003500060 H00702003700044 H00702004600028 H00702004800024 H00702101000056 H00901301900034 H00901302200018 H00901402000036 H00901500800032 H00901503300016 H00901703900010 H00901704500022 H00901704700022 H00901705000044 H00901705100024 H00901800400034 H00902100900028 H00902100900034 H00902101000010 H00902201000024 H00902201300036 H00902201900020 H00902201900058 H00902501300018 H00902501300028 H00902501300040 H00903100400016 H00903100400072 H00903100500026 H01000101200056 H01000102200026 H01000201600016 H01000202600024 H01000302900056 H01001102500056 H01001200900042 H01001200900066 H01001201000010 H01001501400082 H01001800800052 H01002000800050 H01002001000014 H01002301000034 H01002400900042 H01100105100074 H01100200800078 H01100203200042 H01100302400014 H0110030240